      "When you have an urge to smoke while using nicotine replacement therapy, you may be able to adjust your medication to get more relief. People using a lower-dose patch may be able to switch to a higher-dose patch, or combine the patch with a faster-acting product like mini-lozenges or gum. If you are taking varenicline or bupropion and still struggle with urges, talk with your healthcare provider about your options.",
