      "Some quit-smoking medicines do not contain nicotine and work on the brain in different ways. Bupropion is one such non-nicotine medication that has many effects on the brain, including helping people quit smoking. It decreases craving and other nicotine withdrawal symptoms, making it easier to stay off cigarettes.",
