      "Varenicline makes it harder to get a nicotine 'buzz' from smoking. It does this by blocking the brain receptors where nicotine would normally attach, so cigarettes become less rewarding. This dual action of easing withdrawal while blunting the pleasurable effects of smoking is what makes the medication useful for quitting."
