      "Set a quit date within one to two weeks of deciding to quit. Giving yourself time to prepare helps you build the confidence and skills you need to stay smokefree, but avoid choosing a date too far in the future because a distant date can weaken your motivation. If you are struggling to commit to a date, a Practice Quit program lets you rehearse quitting for 1, 3, or 5 days before the real attempt.",
