      "Nicotine withdrawal symptoms typically peak within the first few days after quitting and then subside over the following weeks. Some people experience symptoms that last longer, and genetics can influence how intense and how prolonged withdrawal feels from person to person. This means a slower or harder withdrawal for some individuals is biologically real, not a lack of willpower.",
