    "retrievalDate": "2026-06-10",
    "chunks": [
      "People who use e-cigarettes can become addicted to nicotine, which makes quitting vaping challenging. According to the CDC, quitting vaping resembles quitting smoking because both involve nicotine dependence and can produce withdrawal symptoms. Learning strategies to manage nicotine withdrawal symptoms is a core part of a successful quit attempt.",
      "Free telephone quitline coaching is available for people quitting vaping or smoking. Call 1-800-QUIT-NOW for English support, 1-800-DEJELO-YA for Spanish, 1-800-838-8917 for Mandarin and Cantonese, 1-800-566-5564 for Korean, or 1-800-778-8440 for Vietnamese.",
      "Several free text-message and digital quit programs exist for nicotine cessation. These include SmokefreeTXT, SmokefreeTXT for Teens, and SmokefreeNATIVE text programs, the quitSTART mobile app, and online tools at CDC.gov/Quit, Smokefree.gov, and Teen.smokefree.gov. Creating a personalized quit plan through smokefree.gov is a recommended first step.",
      "The CDC recommends consulting a healthcare provider when quitting nicotine, both to discuss medication options and to get help managing withdrawal symptoms. Combining counseling with medication produces the best cessation outcomes, better than either approach alone.",
      "The FDA has approved seven medications to help people quit smoking, and using these medications can double the chance that someone will quit smoking for good. In contrast, the FDA has not approved any e-cigarette product as a smoking cessation aid. While some studies suggest nicotine-containing e-cigarettes may help some adults quit smoking compared to non-nicotine versions, the long-term health effects of using e-cigarettes are still uncertain.",
      "Dual use, meaning using both e-cigarettes and regular cigarettes at the same time, is not an effective way to quit smoking. The CDC warns that dual use may result in greater exposure to toxins than using either product alone, so people who switch to e-cigarettes should fully stop smoking cigarettes rather than continuing both."
    ]
